      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_social_care_wales">Social Care Wales</xref>
 is a statutory body with regulatory powers in Wales, established by the National Assembly for Wales through the Regulation and Inspection of Social Care (Wales) Act 2016.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_social_care_wales">Social Care Wales</xref>'s main objective is to protect, promote and maintain the safety and well-being of the public in Wales.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_social_care_wales">Social Care Wales</xref>'s role is in promoting and maintaining:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>high standards in the provision of care and support services,</p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
high standards of conduct and practice among 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_social_care_worker">Social Care Workers</xref>,                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
high standards in the training of 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_social_care_worker">Social Care Workers</xref>, and                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
public confidence in 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_social_care_worker">Social Care Workers</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_social_care_wales">Social Care Wales</xref>, see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_social_care_wales">Social Care Wales</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://socialcare.wales/about"
               scope="external"
               format="html">About</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
